SIMPLE: tinct
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tinct
<hw>Tinct</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>tinctus</ets>,
p. p. of <ets>tingere</ets> to tinge. See <er>Tinge</er>.]</ety>
<def>Tined; tinged.</def> <mark>[Archaic]</mark>
<rj><au>Spenser.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tinct</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Tinct
<hw>Tinct</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See <er>Tint</er>.]</ety>
<def>Color; tinge; tincture; tint.</def> <mark>[Archaic]</mark>
⟦ldquo⟧Blue of heaven's own <xex>tinct</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>All the devices blazoned on the shield,⟦br⟧
In their own <qex>tinct</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Tennyson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tinct</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Tinct
<hw>Tinct</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[See <er>Tinge</er>.]</ety>
<def>To color or stain; to imblue; to tint.</def> <mark>[Archaic]</mark>
<rj><au>Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tinctorial</ent>⟦br⟧
